{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id79fa3c28-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s5107b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"5107b"},"text":"§ 5107b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Transition to management of American lobster fishery by Commission","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79fa3c29-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s5107b/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Temporary limits","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of this chapter or of the Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1801"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 1801","children":[],"tail":" et seq.), if no regulations have been issued under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s5103/b"},"text":"section 5103(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" by "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-12-31"},"text":"December 31, 1997","children":[],"tail":", to implement a coastal fishery management plan for American lobster, then the Secretary shall issue interim regulations before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-03-01"},"text":"March 1, 1998","children":[],"tail":", that will prohibit any vessel that takes lobsters in the exclusive economic zone by a method other than pots or traps from landing lobsters (or any parts thereof) at any location within the United States in excess of—"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79fa3c2a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s5107b/a/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 100 lobsters (or parts thereof) for each fishing trip of 24 hours or less duration (up to a maximum of 500 lobsters, or parts thereof, during any 5-day period); or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id79fa3c2b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s5107b/a/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" 500 lobsters (or parts thereof) for a fishing trip of 5 days or longer.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79fa3c2c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s5107b/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Secretary to monitor landings","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Before ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-01-01"},"text":"January 1, 1998","children":[],"tail":", the Secretary shall monitor, on a timely basis, landings of American lobster, and, if the Secretary determines that catches from vessels that take lobsters in the exclusive economic zone by a method other than pots or traps have increased significantly, then the Secretary may, consistent with the national standards in section 301 of the Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1851"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 1851","children":[],"tail":"], and after opportunity for public comment and consultation with the Atlantic States Marine Fisheries Commission, implement regulations under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s5103/b"},"text":"section 5103(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" that are necessary for the conservation of American lobster."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"id79fa3c2d-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s5107b/c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"c"},"text":"(c)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Regulations to remain in effect until plan implemented","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Regulations issued under subsection (a) or (b) shall remain in effect until the Secretary implements regulations under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s5103/b"},"text":"section 5103(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":" to implement a coastal fishery management plan for American lobster."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id79fa3c2e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/206/tVIII/s810"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–206, title VIII, § 810","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/297/tIV/s404/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–297, title IV, § 404(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/3620"},"text":"110 Stat. 3620","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/555/tI/s122/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–555, title I, § 122(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-12-21"},"text":"Dec. 21, 2000","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/114/2766"},"text":"114 Stat. 2766","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id79fa3c2f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id79fa3c30-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"id79fa3c31-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This chapter, referred to in subsec. (a), was in the original “this Act”, and was translated as reading “this title”, meaning title VIII of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/206"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–206","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1993-12-20"},"text":"Dec. 20, 1993","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/107/2447"},"text":"107 Stat. 2447","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to this chapter. For complete classification of title VIII to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s5101"},"text":"section 5101 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Magnuson-Stevens Fishery Conservation and Management Act, referred to in subsec. (a), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/265"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–265","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-04-13"},"text":"Apr. 13, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/331"},"text":"90 Stat. 331","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 38 (§ 1801 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1801"},"text":"section 1801 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id79fa3c32-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/206/s810"},"text":"section 810 of Pub. L. 103–206","children":[],"tail":", which repealed "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/613/s9"},"text":"section 9 of Pub. L. 98–613","children":[],"tail":" set out in a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s1851"},"text":"section 1851 of this title","children":[],"tail":", was renumbered section 812 by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/297"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–297","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id79fa3c33-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2000—Subsecs. (a), (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/555"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–555","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Magnuson-Stevens Fishery” for “Magnuson Fishery”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
